---
description: Agent behavior anti-drift — scope control, context limits, change summaries
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
When context exceeds 10 files, stop and ask which to prioritize.
Do not refactor code that is outside the scope of the request.
When modifying existing code, preserve the existing style unless asked to refactor.
Never delete or overwrite existing functionality silently.

After completing a task, summarize:
1. What was changed
2. What was NOT changed (and why)
3. Any follow-up actions recommended

If a task requires more than 5 files to change, break it into steps
and confirm before proceeding.
Reset context understanding when switching between projects.

When unsure about intent, ASK one targeted clarifying question
before writing a single line of code. Never assume and proceed.
